# SEO & GEO Standards

## Every Page Must Have

1. **`generateMetadata()`** returning:
   - `title` (unique, max 60 chars)
   - `description` (unique, 150-160 chars)
   - `canonical` URL
   - `alternates.languages` with hreflang for IT + EN + x-default
   - `openGraph` (title, description, url, image, locale, type)
   - `twitter` (card, title, description, image)
   - `robots` (index: true, follow: true)

2. **StructuredData** component with appropriate schema:
   - Homepage: `Organization`
   - Service pages: `Service` + `Organization`
   - Case study pages: `Article` or `CaseStudy` (custom) + `Organization`

3. **Hreflang tags** via `alternates.languages`:
   ```
   "en": baseUrl/en/path
   "it": baseUrl/it/path
   "x-default": baseUrl/en/path
   ```

## URL Slug Rules

- Lowercase only
- Hyphen-separated (no underscores, no camelCase)
- Max 3 words (e.g., `operating-partner`, not `ai-native-operating-partner-service`)
- Must not collide with reserved slugs in `src/lib/reserved-slugs.ts`

## Internal Linking

- Every service page links back to homepage.
- Homepage links to all published service/case-study pages.
- Case study pages link to the relevant service page.
- Use `next/link` with locale-aware paths.
